### Docker Networking ###

1. Bridge Network       (It is the defauls network provided by docker networks we can create network according to the requirements).

2. Host Network         (It can take Ip from the host machine on which the docker deaon is running).

3. ipvlan Network       (This network we can assigne or define which Ip's are can be assing to the container).

4. Overlay Network      (This network is used to connect multiple docker deamon's within the orgainzation).

5. MACvlan Network      (This network can be use by the mac of any wireless device Eg, home wifi unable to trace).

6. None Network         (This network is use when we don't want to assigne any network to the container).